WEBVTT

00:02.437 --> 00:04.743
♪

00:25.416 --> 00:28.680
You got any room on
that couch? You got a naked
girl coming right at you.

00:28.724 --> 00:31.727
Bring it on.
SAM: Go on.

00:31.770 --> 00:33.381
Go on.

00:33.424 --> 00:35.470
[REX LAUGHING]

00:35.513 --> 00:37.733
REX: Come here, you little
monkey. Will you please
get her dressed?

00:37.776 --> 00:39.691
Let's clean up
before Bama gets here.

00:39.735 --> 00:42.172
I don't want her telling me
I'm a lousy housekeeper.

00:42.216 --> 00:44.522
Oh, shoot. I gotta get ready.
We're supposed
to be at the bank.

00:44.566 --> 00:46.481
Why do you have
to go to the bank?

00:46.524 --> 00:48.135
Because we need money
for stuff, like your braces.

00:48.178 --> 00:51.094
But I don't want braces.
I want a video game player.

00:51.138 --> 00:53.531
Charlie, your mama's gonna
tell you something true.

00:53.575 --> 00:56.882
No matter what you choose
to do or be, life is easier
if you're pretty.

00:56.926 --> 01:00.103
It does a girl no good
to be good at video games.

01:00.147 --> 01:02.714
Knock, knock. Hey, y'all.
Hi, Mama.

01:02.758 --> 01:04.238
Hey, Bama.
Hey, Bama.

01:04.281 --> 01:07.719
It's hotter than a fur coat
in Marfa out there.

01:07.763 --> 01:10.157
Guess you're just gonna
let them watch TV all day.

01:10.200 --> 01:12.898
Oh, Mama, please don't start.
I'm trying to get ready.

01:12.942 --> 01:16.424
Hey, Mama, that laundry
was folded. It will be
when I get through.

01:20.254 --> 01:21.820
Hi, Bama.

01:21.864 --> 01:24.562
Jenna. One, two. Whoo!

01:24.606 --> 01:27.783
I'm so glad to see you.
Give Bama a great big kiss
right there.

01:27.826 --> 01:30.481
Look how big you're getting.
REX: How's it going, Cassie?

01:30.525 --> 01:34.355
Well, I'm a two-pack-a-dayer
trying to quit smoking,
that's how it's going.

01:34.398 --> 01:36.879
You know what gum
with nicotine tastes like?

01:36.922 --> 01:39.142
Gum with nicotine.

01:39.186 --> 01:40.752
How's the knee?

01:40.796 --> 01:43.320
Oh, doesn't work
and keeps me up all night.

01:43.364 --> 01:46.845
Sounds like my
last two husbands. Heh.

01:46.889 --> 01:49.370
What are you gonna do
if the bank turns you down?

01:49.413 --> 01:51.067
No idea.

01:51.111 --> 01:53.765
Well, it ain't
a sin to be poor,
but it's damned inconvenient.

01:53.809 --> 01:56.333
Well, what do y'all think?

01:56.377 --> 01:58.770
You're either a magician
or twins.

01:58.814 --> 02:02.165
CHARLIE: Mama,
you look pretty.
REX: You sure do.

02:02.209 --> 02:04.733
It's gonna be harder for
the banker to turn you down
in that outfit.

02:04.776 --> 02:08.476
That's what I'm counting on.
Like you said, "Use it
until you lose it."

02:08.519 --> 02:10.478
Heck, I've lost it
and I'm still using it.

02:10.520 --> 02:11.696
[SNIFFING]

02:11.740 --> 02:14.177
What smells like pumpkin pie?
Oh, it's me.

02:14.221 --> 02:17.398
These scientists did
a test and figured out
that the smell of pumpkin

02:17.441 --> 02:20.836
brings blood flow to a man's
you-know-what faster
than anything else.

02:20.879 --> 02:23.404
Where'd you hear that?
I read it in some
woman's magazine.

02:23.447 --> 02:25.971
August 2006 issue.
Reese Witherspoon
was on the cover.

02:26.015 --> 02:27.930
Rex, come on, we gotta scoot.

02:27.973 --> 02:29.627
Babies, be good to your Bama.

02:29.671 --> 02:32.848
Bye, Mama.
Bye, Mama.

02:32.891 --> 02:35.981
Ow! Dang it.
I just broke my nail.

02:36.025 --> 02:37.896
Sugar, no one's looking
at your nails.

02:37.940 --> 02:41.465
Been married to you
nine years, I haven't gotten
to your nails yet.

02:41.509 --> 02:42.901
Come on.

02:42.945 --> 02:45.730
Now, Sam, don't slouch
like you do. Knockers up.

02:47.515 --> 02:50.518
I am so nervous.
Yeah, me too.

02:50.561 --> 02:52.215
Let me unbutton these.

02:52.259 --> 02:54.217
Just in case he's gay.

02:54.261 --> 02:55.871
Well, I did say
"whatever it takes."

02:55.914 --> 02:59.396
Oh, baby, how did
we get ourselves
into such an awful mess?

02:59.440 --> 03:02.269
A lot of people asking
those questions these days.

03:02.312 --> 03:04.314
Samantha Horton.

03:04.358 --> 03:07.752
Hell's bells, I do not need
Carol Reed telling me
how perfect her life is.

03:07.796 --> 03:09.972
Hey, I dumped her for you.
You got the big prize.

03:10.015 --> 03:11.626
Don't tell her
why we're here.

03:11.669 --> 03:14.890
Hey, Carol. Hi.
It's been forever.

03:14.933 --> 03:16.761
Don't you look pretty.

03:16.805 --> 03:19.503
I do believe you were wearing
that same dress
the last time I saw you.

03:19.547 --> 03:20.896
Well, aren't you observant.

03:20.939 --> 03:23.420
Jim and I were just here
on business,

03:23.464 --> 03:26.989
but tomorrow we're off
to Hawaii and then we're going
to New York

03:27.032 --> 03:28.773
to do a little shopping.

03:28.817 --> 03:31.254
We all got to stimulate
the economy, right?

03:31.298 --> 03:33.691
Bless your heart,
always thinking of others.

03:33.735 --> 03:35.432
Bye-bye.

03:35.476 --> 03:37.260
REX: Y'all travel safe.
Will do.

03:37.304 --> 03:39.001
Bye.

03:39.044 --> 03:42.265
Mrs. Horton, Mr. Horton,
please have a seat.

03:42.309 --> 03:43.397
Thank you.

03:43.440 --> 03:47.879
Well, we're here about,
uh, this letter.

03:50.665 --> 03:53.450
Well, I'd say
it's a bit more than a letter.

03:53.494 --> 03:55.757
This is a notice of intent
to foreclose.

03:55.800 --> 03:58.629
Yes, and we know we're
seriously behind
in our payments,

03:58.673 --> 04:00.979
but the rates
suddenly jumped so high...

04:01.023 --> 04:02.894
As adjustable rates do.

04:02.938 --> 04:06.463
Mr. Sweeny, it's like I was
trying to tell you
on the telephone,

04:06.507 --> 04:08.987
my physical therapy job
just got phased out

04:09.031 --> 04:11.512
and Rex here, well,
he hurt his knee so bad

04:11.555 --> 04:14.297
that he had to quit his
construction job
and get surgery.

04:14.341 --> 04:15.994
We're just trying to pay back
the medical bills.

04:16.038 --> 04:18.345
The healing's been
a whole lot slower than
I'd hoped.

04:18.387 --> 04:21.348
I sympathize, but mortgage
payments must be maintained...

04:21.391 --> 04:24.786
It's not just about the
mortgage. We're strapped.

04:24.829 --> 04:26.483
Completely.

04:26.527 --> 04:31.401
Getting dinner on the table,
it's hard. We need more time.

04:31.445 --> 04:33.925
But, Mrs. Horton,
I can't really give you...

04:33.969 --> 04:35.971
You can call me Sam.

04:37.102 --> 04:38.800
Sam.

04:42.543 --> 04:44.632
That's an interesting scent
you're wearing.

04:44.675 --> 04:47.504
You like it?
Very much.

04:49.854 --> 04:53.118
But, uh, there's nothing
I can do.

04:53.162 --> 04:55.425
With the current financial
situation,

04:55.469 --> 04:58.907
this bank must take a
zero-tolerance position
on non-payment.

04:58.950 --> 05:00.996
But what about the government
bailing you out
to help us out?

05:01.039 --> 05:02.345
Where's the help?

05:02.389 --> 05:04.347
All I can tell you

05:04.391 --> 05:07.437
is that unless
we receive payment
on the 15th of this month,

05:07.481 --> 05:10.353
foreclosure
proceedings will begin.

05:10.397 --> 05:12.399
And we'll lose our home.
Yes.

05:12.442 --> 05:14.749
That is what
foreclosure means.

05:14.792 --> 05:16.881
I'm sorry.
SAM: No, you're not.

05:18.013 --> 05:20.363
Not really.

05:20.407 --> 05:22.713
Even though
you're plenty at
fault here too.

05:22.757 --> 05:24.106
The day we met you,

05:24.149 --> 05:27.152
you told us that a subprime
ARM loan made good sense

05:27.196 --> 05:29.503
and not to worry
about rate adjustments

05:29.546 --> 05:31.548
because we would be able
to refinance
before the loan resets.

05:31.592 --> 05:33.681
Then you told us it would be
"advantageous

05:33.724 --> 05:37.075
for us to enhance our income
statement to help facilitate
the approving process."

05:37.119 --> 05:39.991
Those were your words,
exactly.

05:40.035 --> 05:44.169
Now, I don't think any of us
remembers
exactly what was said.

05:44.213 --> 05:45.475
She does.

05:45.519 --> 05:47.564
You were wearing
a black-and-gray coat,

05:47.608 --> 05:49.566
with a taupe shirt
and a cream tie.

05:49.610 --> 05:51.742
It had a quarter-sized
hot sauce stain on it.

05:51.786 --> 05:53.701
You were worried
because you were

05:53.744 --> 05:55.616
getting ready to
take your photo ID.

05:58.053 --> 06:01.535
There's the tie
and there's the stain.

06:01.578 --> 06:05.539
Now, what exactly
don't I remember, exactly?

06:09.891 --> 06:11.719
Like I said.

06:14.156 --> 06:16.811
At least you got
a month's extension.
It's something.

06:16.854 --> 06:19.466
Is it?
What's gonna make it better
next month?

06:19.509 --> 06:21.424
Chocolate milk shakes
and cheese fries.

06:21.468 --> 06:24.427
That will make it better
for about five minutes,
but I'll take it.

06:24.471 --> 06:26.211
Here's my application.

06:26.255 --> 06:28.953
I know you guys aren't hiring,
but if you could
have the manager

06:28.997 --> 06:31.478
Thanks.
You're really desperate, huh?

06:31.521 --> 06:33.567
I would join the Army
if I could wear heels.

06:33.610 --> 06:36.613
We'd hire you at
the bar if we could.
I know you would.

06:36.657 --> 06:39.007
There's nothing
promising for Rex?
Not a thing.

06:39.050 --> 06:40.835
Nobody's even hiring.

06:40.878 --> 06:43.533
If there were any
construction jobs,
they're not gonna go for a guy

06:43.577 --> 06:46.841
Gosh,
this must be killing him.
You know men and pride.

06:46.884 --> 06:48.233
Men are complicated.

06:48.277 --> 06:50.105
No, they're not. Men are easy.

06:50.148 --> 06:52.803
"I'm thirsty,"
"I'm hungry," "I'm horny."
That's men.

06:52.847 --> 06:55.458
Although not necessarily
in that order.

06:55.502 --> 06:57.765
You guys, I never thought
I'd say anything
quite as sappy

06:57.808 --> 07:00.811
as "it was not supposed
to turn out this way,"
but it wasn't.

07:00.855 --> 07:02.465
When they were
scouting Rex for UT,

07:02.509 --> 07:03.945
I already had
the drapes picked out

07:03.988 --> 07:05.599
You weren't crazy.

07:05.642 --> 07:09.472
Handsome white running back
is worth his weight in gold.

07:09.516 --> 07:12.127
I just thought we were
gonna be the next
Angie Harmon and Jason Sehorn.

07:12.170 --> 07:14.564
Then he got knocked down.
You got knocked up.

07:14.608 --> 07:16.697
Yeah.

07:16.740 --> 07:18.873
Hey, wait a minute.
Here's something.

07:18.916 --> 07:21.528
"Kind Touch Health Spa.
Licensed massage therapists."

07:21.571 --> 07:23.051
I'm licensed.

07:23.094 --> 07:25.532
I don't know how you do that,
touching stranger's bodies.

07:25.575 --> 07:28.056
It's just skin.
It makes them feel better.

07:28.099 --> 07:30.493
Doesn't say they're hiring,
but it's worth a call.

07:30.537 --> 07:32.930
It's all the way in Lareena.
It's more than
an hour's drive.

07:32.974 --> 07:34.671
Well, there's nothing here.

07:34.715 --> 07:36.760
You were smart to go
and become a lawyer.

07:36.804 --> 07:38.893
My mom said
I was too pretty
for law school.

07:38.936 --> 07:41.156
My mama said I was too skinny
to get a husband.

07:41.199 --> 07:43.027
My mom said to
always wear lipstick,

07:43.071 --> 07:44.942
even if you're just
going to the market.

07:44.986 --> 07:46.988
Well, to Texas moms.

07:47.031 --> 07:49.120
Texas moms.
Texas moms.

07:50.165 --> 07:52.733
♪♪

08:22.632 --> 08:23.938
[DOOR CHIMES RINGING]

08:23.981 --> 08:25.853
Your usual time,
you little devil.

08:25.896 --> 08:28.290
Okay, I've got to go now.

08:28.333 --> 08:29.770
All right, bye-bye.

08:29.813 --> 08:31.815
Hi, there. Can I help you?
Hi.

08:31.859 --> 08:34.861
My name's Samantha Horton,
and I called about
the massage therapy interview?

08:34.905 --> 08:36.211
Oh, that's right.

08:36.254 --> 08:38.126
Here's my resume.
Hi.

08:38.169 --> 08:39.996
Hi there. Well, I'm Jacie.
Hello.

08:40.041 --> 08:42.739
And this here is
my partner, Doreen.

08:42.783 --> 08:45.350
Good morning.
Gosh, you are
a pretty little thing.

08:45.394 --> 08:47.701
Thank you.
And I can spot
a pageant smile.

08:47.744 --> 08:50.007
What did you win?
I was Miss Bixby Hills.

08:50.051 --> 08:53.010
Runner-up, Miss Piedmont.
I dropped my baton.

08:53.054 --> 08:54.838
Well, I entered in Miss Texas,

08:54.882 --> 08:57.754
but then I got
pregnant and married.
Now I got three kids.

08:57.798 --> 09:00.627
I'm dying to have babies.
You were smart to start young.

09:00.670 --> 09:03.020
I'm trained in shiatsu,
and deep tissue,

09:03.064 --> 09:05.109
but I can pretty much
do any kind of massage
y'all want.

09:05.153 --> 09:07.372
Well, look at you.

09:07.416 --> 09:11.289
I'm a real fast learner,
and I'm just
desperate for a job.

09:12.682 --> 09:14.118
Can you start tomorrow?

09:14.162 --> 09:15.903
Really? That's it?

09:15.946 --> 09:17.687
Pretty much, baby.

09:17.731 --> 09:19.602
Thank you.

09:19.646 --> 09:22.692
SAM: Who's starving?
I could eat a buttered monkey.

09:22.736 --> 09:23.867
Yay! Breakfast for supper.

09:23.911 --> 09:26.087
Yeah, we're celebrating
Mama's new job.

09:27.175 --> 09:29.743
So now I can
play flag football?

09:29.786 --> 09:31.353
Flag football is
way down on the list

09:31.396 --> 09:33.224
of things we need
to be paying for.

09:33.268 --> 09:36.314
Please?
Brady, it's like
$100 just to register.

09:36.358 --> 09:39.361
Then there's the team photo
and equipment. And what if
you break your glasses?

09:39.404 --> 09:42.016
BRADY: But...
Conversation is over.

09:42.059 --> 09:44.627
Hey, hon,
I didn't hear your motorcycle.

09:44.671 --> 09:46.411
That's because I sold it.

09:46.455 --> 09:47.978
Rex, you loved that thing.

09:48.022 --> 09:51.634
Yeah, I kind of like
having electricity too.

09:51.678 --> 09:54.855
Baby, I know that wasn't easy.
CASSIE: Good riddance.

09:54.898 --> 09:57.379
You know what
doctors call them?
Donor-cycles.

09:57.422 --> 10:00.687
Are we rich now?
No.

10:00.730 --> 10:04.734
Hey,
sweetheart, what's it like
at that Kind Touch Health Spa?

10:04.778 --> 10:07.041
What's it like?
BRADY: Oh, no, a bee.

10:07.084 --> 10:09.130
Watch out, Brady,
they can smell your fear.

10:09.173 --> 10:11.132
REX: It's all right, I got it.SAM: Hey. Mama.

10:11.175 --> 10:14.701
You know what,
it was real nice.
Rich clients, big tips.

10:14.744 --> 10:15.919
Yeah?

10:15.963 --> 10:18.008
Maybe I should ditch my job
at the salon

10:18.052 --> 10:19.836
and come rub some backs
with you.

10:19.880 --> 10:23.666
Unless they're
mole-y or hairy.
Woman, you wax hoo-has.

10:23.710 --> 10:26.887
Yeah, I remove the hair,
but I don't mess with it.

10:26.930 --> 10:28.932
What's hoo-has?
Nothing.

10:28.976 --> 10:31.413
Daddy, what is a hoo-ha?

10:31.456 --> 10:35.199
[ADULTS LAUGHING]

10:35.243 --> 10:37.767
[SINGING]
Camptown ladies sing this song

10:37.811 --> 10:40.161
Hoo-has, hoo-has

10:40.204 --> 10:42.293
Camptown track
is five miles long

10:42.337 --> 10:44.078
Oh, hoo-ha day

10:44.121 --> 10:45.862
Hi. Here I am.

10:45.906 --> 10:48.299
Oh, hey, honey. Welcome.

10:48.343 --> 10:51.346
Why don't you come on back
and meet
the other girls, okay?

10:51.389 --> 10:53.304
We got a bit of
a lull right now,

10:53.348 --> 10:56.830
but when that Cowboys-Redskins
game is done, we are
gonna be plenty busy.

10:57.308 --> 10:58.788
Come on.

10:58.832 --> 10:59.963
Okay.

11:00.007 --> 11:02.139
All right.

11:02.183 --> 11:03.445
Here we go.

11:03.488 --> 11:04.664
[DOOR LOCK BEEPING]

11:06.317 --> 11:09.233
Okay, ladies, say hi to Sam.

11:09.277 --> 11:11.845
Hey, honey, welcome back.
Hi.

11:11.888 --> 11:15.109
Okay, now, just real quick,
I started this
business 15 years ago.

11:15.152 --> 11:17.502
I wanted to be a novelist,
and I still do,

11:17.546 --> 11:19.896
but this pays the bills
a whole lot better.

11:19.940 --> 11:21.506
Doreen used to be a dancer.

11:21.550 --> 11:24.031
Well, cruise ships mostly,
but some dinner theatre.

11:24.074 --> 11:26.120
Now, she's been partners
with me for 10 years.

11:26.163 --> 11:27.338
Isn't that right?
Yeah.

11:27.382 --> 11:29.732
Tanya's been with us for...
Six.

11:29.776 --> 11:32.822
Six,
that's right, and she is also
an amazing tattoo artist.

11:32.866 --> 11:36.347
Oh, and this here is Emma,
our
barely-legal-looking newbie.

11:36.391 --> 11:39.350
How long you
been here, sweetie?
Uh, two months today.

11:39.394 --> 11:41.178
So nice.

11:41.222 --> 11:43.180
Hey,
hon, you got a client in 4,
why don't you scoot on over.

11:43.224 --> 11:44.486
All right.
JACIE: Okay.

11:44.529 --> 11:47.358
And you're all licensed
massage therapists?

11:47.402 --> 11:51.319
Sure,
yeah, we all have licenses,
and we all give massage.

11:51.362 --> 11:54.757
It's a teensy
bit more than that.
What do you mean?

11:54.801 --> 11:57.238
Well, like my writing teacher

11:57.281 --> 11:59.327
"Why don't you show me,
not tell me?"

11:59.370 --> 12:01.285
Come on over here,
I'll show you.

12:03.853 --> 12:06.029
Let me just
get these open here.

12:07.117 --> 12:10.077
Hi, Richard.

12:10.120 --> 12:11.948
This is one of
those two-way jobs,

12:11.992 --> 12:14.821
you know, like they have
in all the cop shows.

12:14.864 --> 12:17.084
RICHARD: How are you doing?
Pretty good.

12:17.127 --> 12:19.303
How are you?
RICHARD: I'm great.

12:20.087 --> 12:21.828
Oh, I love that SVU.

12:21.871 --> 12:24.569
I think Mariska Hargitay,
she's just darling.

12:24.613 --> 12:26.528
And her mama is
Jayne Mansfield,

12:26.571 --> 12:28.530
so you know those
breasts are real.

12:28.573 --> 12:30.314
Now,
for safety, we always bring

12:30.358 --> 12:32.186
the first-time
clients into this room.

12:32.229 --> 12:35.406
It's above board, nobody does
anything they're
not comfortable with.

12:35.450 --> 12:37.104
You understand?

12:42.544 --> 12:43.937
Wow.

12:44.633 --> 12:46.374
You understand?

12:47.288 --> 12:49.246
Yeah, I guess.

12:49.290 --> 12:50.944
Okay.

12:52.467 --> 12:54.904
♪♪

13:02.477 --> 13:04.479
What am I gonna do now?

13:06.176 --> 13:08.613
I guess that's why they didn't
show me around the first day.

13:08.657 --> 13:10.528
Wanted to ease me into it.

13:10.572 --> 13:13.923
Guess I'll have to
find something else,
or maybe Rex will get a job

13:13.967 --> 13:17.274
or maybe that
lottery ticket I've got
in my purse has three

13:19.189 --> 13:21.017
[PHONE RINGING]

13:21.061 --> 13:22.584
Hey, Dee, what's up?

13:22.627 --> 13:25.326
It's Rex. You kind of need
to come pick him up.

13:25.369 --> 13:27.154
He's in no condition to drive.

13:27.197 --> 13:30.113
You know how it gets in here
when the Cowboys lose.

13:30.157 --> 13:32.159
I'm on my way.

13:34.639 --> 13:36.859
♪♪

13:36.903 --> 13:39.862
Dee, isn't it hard being
on your feet in
your condition?

13:39.906 --> 13:41.733
I'm used to it.

13:41.777 --> 13:45.172
Heck, four kids in five years,
