a little too much?

31:46.252 --> 31:49.733
Dee, come on. You know I've
always dreamt of not having
to look at price tags.

31:49.777 --> 31:51.474
And Rex doesn't
suspect anything?

31:51.518 --> 31:54.695
I mean,
the watch, the earrings,
the necklace?

31:54.738 --> 31:57.089
What do you tell him?
That they're all fake.

31:57.132 --> 31:58.960
Come on.
Men don't know from jewelry.

31:59.004 --> 32:01.093
Well, that's the truth.

32:01.136 --> 32:03.573
Know what's weird?
Nobody even
wants an explanation.

32:03.617 --> 32:05.053
It's like I'm Santa Claus.

32:05.097 --> 32:07.360
Just as long
as I keep
giving them presents,

32:07.403 --> 32:10.319
they can see me soaring
through the sky
with flying reindeer.

32:12.756 --> 32:15.803
Don't worry,
I know what I'm doing.

32:19.676 --> 32:22.201
♪♪

32:32.080 --> 32:33.647
You awake?

32:36.258 --> 32:37.738
Yeah.

32:39.479 --> 32:41.611
I can't sleep.

32:41.655 --> 32:43.352
Me too.

32:43.831 --> 32:45.311
What's wrong?

32:47.052 --> 32:48.705
It's just...

32:52.492 --> 32:56.626
Look,
I'm happy you're working,

32:56.670 --> 33:02.458
and I'm trying to keep
some perspective on this,

33:05.287 --> 33:09.378
but it's
killing me that you're
the breadwinner and I'm not.

33:09.422 --> 33:10.553
Baby.

33:10.597 --> 33:13.774
No, I always said
that I'd protect you,

33:13.817 --> 33:18.170
that I would take care of you.

33:25.351 --> 33:26.700
You want a massage?

33:26.743 --> 33:28.180
[CHUCKLES]

33:28.223 --> 33:31.139
No. You've been
doing that all day.

33:34.795 --> 33:37.537
Not to anyone
who looks like you.

33:46.459 --> 33:48.113
Yeah.

33:58.427 --> 33:59.776
[MOANS]

34:02.170 --> 34:05.217
Hey.

34:05.260 --> 34:10.309
I'm sorry about what happened
at the bar the other night.
I mean it.

34:16.880 --> 34:18.578
I love you.

34:20.319 --> 34:22.581
I love you too, girl.

34:27.761 --> 34:29.850
Merry Christmas.
Merry Christmas.

34:34.246 --> 34:37.118
Jim.
Sam.

34:37.161 --> 34:39.773
What are you doing here?
What are you doing here?

34:39.815 --> 34:42.428
What do you
think I'm doing here?

34:42.471 --> 34:44.081
Well, this is embarrassing.

34:45.779 --> 34:48.521
Well, I won't tell
if you won't tell.

34:48.563 --> 34:50.871
There's nothing to tell.
Nothing happened.
I know your wife.

34:50.914 --> 34:53.178
So what?
She's treats you like dirt.

34:53.221 --> 34:55.310
Don't you wanna
stick it to her?

34:55.353 --> 34:58.400
Not by you sticking it to me.
Now, get on out of here.

34:58.444 --> 35:01.316
Go.
All right.

35:06.626 --> 35:08.541
Hurry up, hurry up.
Santa's been here.

35:08.584 --> 35:10.412
Come on, Mama. Come on, Daddy.

35:10.456 --> 35:12.893
Hurry up, you guys.

35:12.936 --> 35:14.547
Wow. Santa brought all this?

35:14.590 --> 35:16.940
This is way more
than last Christmas.

35:16.984 --> 35:19.421
And I thought y'all
were spoiled before.

35:19.465 --> 35:20.857
Slow down there, kids.

35:20.901 --> 35:23.295
Remember, Christmas is more
than just about presents.

35:23.338 --> 35:26.211
Yeah, right.
Happy birthday, Jesus.

35:26.254 --> 35:29.475
Well, that must have been
some Christmas bonus you got.

35:29.518 --> 35:31.520
Not bad.

35:31.564 --> 35:34.784
But don't you think
you're working
a little too hard?

35:34.828 --> 35:37.265
I'm starting to see lines
on that pretty face.

35:37.309 --> 35:40.616
Mama.
Don't frown,
it makes it worse.

35:40.660 --> 35:42.792
I'm just saying you
look tired, is all.

35:42.836 --> 35:45.621
Well, don't all parents
look tired on
Christmas morning?

35:45.665 --> 35:48.885
Now, go look under that tree
for a little box
with your name on it.

35:48.929 --> 35:51.584
Something very sparkly inside.
Yes, ma'am.

35:53.281 --> 35:55.544
Look at this.

35:56.980 --> 35:59.331
Your present's outside.

36:03.335 --> 36:04.814
SAM: Okay.
What?

36:04.858 --> 36:07.556
What are you doing?
What is this?
Open your eyes.

36:07.600 --> 36:09.689
Surprise.
No, you didn't.

36:09.732 --> 36:11.604
I did.

36:11.647 --> 36:15.564
Oh, Sam, I don't
even know what to say.

36:15.608 --> 36:17.175
I mean, thank you.

36:19.612 --> 36:21.875
I got something for you,

36:21.918 --> 36:24.660
but, wow, next to this...

36:24.704 --> 36:26.314
Oh, what the heck.

36:34.888 --> 36:38.370
Well, "Rex Horton.
Trainee."

36:39.066 --> 36:41.286
It's an exterminating company

36:41.329 --> 36:43.288
and the money's not great,

36:43.331 --> 36:45.246
but did you know
there are more rats

36:45.290 --> 36:46.987
in east Texas than
in New York City?

36:47.030 --> 36:48.510
Sexy.

36:48.554 --> 36:50.730
Don't even get me started
on cockroaches.

36:52.340 --> 36:56.866
It's real good.
No, it's gross.

36:56.910 --> 36:58.259
But it's a start.

37:01.393 --> 37:04.570
Now stay tuned
for your local news,
weather and sports.

37:04.613 --> 37:05.745
Here's Jimmy.

37:09.749 --> 37:14.580
Well,
folks, if you moved to Texas
for the cool summer...

37:14.623 --> 37:16.364
Ooh, there's a bunch
of guys out there.

37:16.408 --> 37:18.453
Who knew this business
had a holiday rush?

37:18.497 --> 37:20.934
A lot of lonely people
this time of year.

37:24.459 --> 37:26.896
No, it can't be.

37:26.940 --> 37:28.289
It can't be.
SAM: What?

37:28.333 --> 37:30.248
What can't it be?

37:31.510 --> 37:32.815
What is it?

37:34.034 --> 37:37.646
It's
the preacher from my church.

37:37.690 --> 37:41.259
He's wearing the brown sweater
the choir gave him
for secret Santa.

37:42.390 --> 37:44.653
I picked out that sweater.

37:48.396 --> 37:50.398
♪♪

37:53.793 --> 37:55.882
I think I'm gonna be sick.

38:15.641 --> 38:18.948
Are you okay?
I don't know.

38:18.992 --> 38:23.649
Well,
go on, then, get out of here.
But where?

38:23.692 --> 38:27.435
I can't go home,
and Idol auditions
aren't for another six months.

38:27.479 --> 38:30.351
Baby, you can always go home.

38:30.395 --> 38:33.789
As a parent,
I always tell my kids...
Will you pray with me?

38:37.663 --> 38:40.056
I gotta get back inside,
but you know what?

38:40.100 --> 38:43.886
That Christian
Fellowship Lodge,
it's right over there.

38:44.844 --> 38:47.586
Say one for me, would you?

39:01.513 --> 39:03.602
♪♪

39:20.793 --> 39:22.664
Excuse me?

39:22.708 --> 39:24.753
So sorry to interrupt,

39:26.233 --> 39:28.409
but I think God
wants me to tell you

39:28.453 --> 39:31.412
what's going on
at that health
spa across the way.

39:31.456 --> 39:33.762
♪♪

39:44.512 --> 39:45.774
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

39:48.081 --> 39:49.604
All right,
all right, all right.

39:51.127 --> 39:53.434
Hey. Hey, I made it.

39:53.478 --> 39:55.523
I made it.

39:55.567 --> 39:57.612
There's 20 seconds left.

39:57.656 --> 40:00.180
You missed Brady's touchdown.
Brady?

40:00.223 --> 40:02.051
Kid covering him
got stung by a bee.

40:02.095 --> 40:04.489
Well, I'm sorry.
It was my job.

40:04.532 --> 40:06.839
I have a job too, Sam.
I'm here.

40:06.882 --> 40:08.275
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

40:08.318 --> 40:11.626
All right, good game.
Hornets, come on, bring it in.

40:11.670 --> 40:13.715
Bring it in.
Sam.

40:15.108 --> 40:16.762
DEE: You okay?
Well, I just...

40:16.805 --> 40:18.981
I can't believe
I missed Brady's touchdown.

40:19.025 --> 40:21.201
Well, I'd love to say
there'll be many more,

40:21.244 --> 40:24.204
but we both know I'd be lying.

40:24.247 --> 40:26.728
Dee, I drove here so fast,
I almost got a ticket.

40:26.772 --> 40:28.469
I swear,
I'm doing everything I can to

40:28.513 --> 40:30.079
keep it together,
but it's too much.

40:30.123 --> 40:33.779
So quit.
I can't.

40:33.822 --> 40:36.172
Money's too good.
The house needs a new roof.

40:36.216 --> 40:38.523
Rex is thinking
about buying into

40:38.566 --> 40:40.699
that company he's
been working for.

40:40.742 --> 40:42.657
I'll quit.

40:42.701 --> 40:44.572
I will. I've got to.

40:45.878 --> 40:49.621
I'm just so tired
of being tired all the time.

40:49.664 --> 40:51.753
I scored a touchdown.
I scored a touchdown.

40:51.797 --> 40:54.103
Brady.
Oh, you got a touchdown.

40:54.147 --> 40:55.801
I'm not scared
of bees anymore.

40:55.844 --> 40:57.933
I scored a touchdown.
I scored a touchdown.

40:57.977 --> 41:00.501
Did you see me?
I did see you, yeah.

41:00.545 --> 41:03.199
I can't wait.
I just can't
wait for the finals.

41:03.243 --> 41:06.159
I scored
the winning touchdown.

41:06.855 --> 41:08.466
Yeah.

41:09.118 --> 41:12.078
[ALARM CLOCK BUZZING]

41:13.732 --> 41:14.950
[ALARM STOPS]

41:14.994 --> 41:16.735
Sam.

41:16.778 --> 41:18.737
Sam, wake up, baby.

41:18.780 --> 41:20.086
Sam.

41:20.826 --> 41:21.914
Hm?

41:22.871 --> 41:24.743
I guess I never
heard the alarm.

41:24.786 --> 41:27.136
I heard it way
out in the garage.

41:27.920 --> 41:29.530
Honey, this is nuts.

41:29.574 --> 41:31.140
Last few weeks,
you've been
wearing yourself out.

41:31.184 --> 41:34.100
You gotta cut
back on the hours.
I'm up.

41:34.143 --> 41:35.971
I'm up.

41:44.676 --> 41:47.809
Hey, have you seen
Emma lately? I haven't
seen her since Christmas.

41:47.853 --> 41:51.291
No, and I miss that
little buttercup, because
it's so crazy around here.

41:51.334 --> 41:54.860
I'll tell you what's crazy,
me sitting here bored
and horny

41:54.903 --> 41:56.818
while Sam's
got three rooms going.

41:56.862 --> 41:59.560
Oh, well, don't go comparing
yourself to others, Tanya.

41:59.604 --> 42:01.301
We all got our own strengths.

42:01.344 --> 42:03.825
Though I gotta say,
Sam's been busy as popcorn.

42:03.869 --> 42:05.131
Yeah.

42:05.174 --> 42:07.220
Guys flying in from Germany
on private jets.

42:07.263 --> 42:08.830
Guys buying her jewelry.

42:08.874 --> 42:10.266
And three, three proposals.

42:10.310 --> 42:13.574
That's gotta be like
some kind of record. Heh, heh.

42:13.618 --> 42:15.794
I can't believe
it's almost 4:00.

42:17.099 --> 42:19.014
Dang it.

42:19.058 --> 42:21.190
Y'all,
why is this always empty?

42:21.234 --> 42:24.237
Sam, you got a new guy in 2,
and Number 4's still waiting.

42:24.280 --> 42:27.196
Well, the last guy
was in real estate,
and he wouldn't stop crying.

42:27.240 --> 42:29.808
I'm sorry. Two seconds,
and I'll be right there.

42:31.679 --> 42:33.289
Well,
I'm sorry, but I gotta know.

42:33.333 --> 42:35.248
What can she be doing
that we're not?

42:35.291 --> 42:37.598
I mean, there's only
so many places
to put things

42:37.642 --> 42:39.252
and so many things
to put in them.

42:43.691 --> 42:46.346
Pecan sandies
with crushed hazelnuts?

42:46.389 --> 42:48.914
I can't believe
you remembered.
Of course I did.

42:48.957 --> 42:50.263
Your Aunt Julie
used to make them

42:50.306 --> 42:51.873
for you when you
went to Alabama.

42:51.917 --> 42:54.920
Amazing. My wife can't even
remember how I like my eggs.

42:54.963 --> 42:56.225
Scrambled. With hot sauce.

42:56.269 --> 42:58.053
Now, did Ruth-Ann
get that part?

42:59.925 --> 43:01.622
What the what?

43:01.666 --> 43:04.233
She wanted the princess role,
but got the funny
fairy godmother.

43:04.277 --> 43:05.713
Well...

43:07.672 --> 43:09.325
you just tell her
that the funny parts

43:09.369 --> 43:11.110
are the ones
everyone remembers.

43:11.937 --> 43:13.112
Bingo.

43:13.155 --> 43:16.028
Lay on down.
Yes, ma'am.

43:24.210 --> 43:27.082
[UPBEAT POP SONG PLAYING
ON STEREO]

43:27.996 --> 43:30.129
[TURNS UP VOLUME]

43:47.015 --> 43:49.148
[CAR HORN HONKING]

43:58.244 --> 44:00.333
[HORN HONKING]

44:12.780 --> 44:14.434
Brandy,
you could have been killed.

44:14.477 --> 44:16.741
Yeah, well,
I'm just having a hard time
staying awake.

44:16.784 --> 44:20.048
I can't have my favorite girl
falling asleep at the wheel.

44:27.969 --> 44:29.884
Is that what I think it is?

44:29.928 --> 44:32.365
It'll keep you going.
Works for me.

44:34.367 --> 44:37.283
Well, no offense,
but I've never
even tried weed,

44:37.326 --> 44:41.113
and I don't wanna
do anything wrong
or highly illegal.

44:42.201 --> 44:44.856
More than I'm doing right now.

44:44.899 --> 44:49.687
Well,
it's there if you need it.

44:51.384 --> 44:52.907
See you next week, Brandy.

44:52.951 --> 44:54.953
Looking forward to it.

45:03.091 --> 45:04.702
[SIGHS]

45:10.446 --> 45:12.013
Wake up, Mama.

45:12.057 --> 45:13.536
Mama.

45:13.580 --> 45:15.800
Wake up.

45:15.843 --> 45:18.846
Mama.
Uh...

45:18.890 --> 45:21.196
Hey.
Mama's gonna turn in early.

45:21.240 --> 45:23.329
Just brush your teeth
and say your prayers, okay?

45:23.372 --> 45:25.374
But you can't sleep.

45:25.418 --> 45:28.856
Tomorrow's the bake sale,
remember?

45:28.900 --> 45:32.468
What?
We're raising
money for the fur.

45:32.512 --> 45:35.863
For the fur?
Yeah, it's
a country that's in trouble.

45:36.821 --> 45:38.866
Oh, you mean Darfur.

45:38.910 --> 45:40.215
I guess.

45:40.259 --> 45:42.043
The bake sale's
a castle theme.

45:42.087 --> 45:43.871
I come up with the idea.

45:47.440 --> 45:49.877
Mama? Are you listening?

45:49.921 --> 45:51.313
Yeah.

45:51.357 --> 45:52.837
I'm up.

45:52.880 --> 45:54.447
I'm up.

45:58.625 --> 46:00.975
♪♪

46:11.899 --> 46:14.162
Okay, I can do this.

46:14.206 --> 46:16.034
I'm a good mother.

46:16.077 --> 46:18.471
This is what good mothers do.

46:20.473 --> 46:21.866
All right.

46:21.909 --> 46:25.434
"With the gray fondant
make castle turrets.

46:25.478 --> 46:29.438
With the green fondant,
place pieces into the mountain

46:29.482 --> 46:31.092
and with a piping..."

46:31.136 --> 46:33.007
[SIGHS]

46:34.182 --> 46:36.097
Wake up, Sam.

46:36.881 --> 46:38.926
Oh, I'm tired.

46:43.148 --> 46:44.976
Okay.

46:49.632 --> 46:51.504
What does that say?

46:59.077 --> 47:01.383
♪♪

47:20.098 --> 47:22.491
Well, what do y'all think?

47:22.535 --> 47:26.365
Wow, Mama, it's perfect.
Wow.

47:26.408 --> 47:29.194
REX: You must have
been up all night.
I was, but it's done.

47:29.237 --> 47:33.285
And you can move the chocolate
drawbridge and
the moat is fudge.

47:33.328 --> 47:35.243
Okay, y'all get ready.

47:36.984 --> 47:38.203
Hey.

47:39.682 --> 47:41.293
You're a great mom.

47:43.556 --> 47:45.340
Bye.

47:46.559 --> 47:48.866
♪♪

47:52.434 --> 47:53.653
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

47:53.696 --> 47:55.089
Sam, honey,
your next client's here.

47:55.133 --> 47:57.222
He's got a flight to catch.

47:57.265 --> 48:00.138
Hey, Sam, you okay?
SAM: Yeah,
I'll be there in a minute.

48:00.181 --> 48:02.009
All right, doll.

48:14.500 --> 48:16.067
[SNIFFLES]

48:26.164 --> 48:28.993
It's really a show
you won't wanna miss.

48:29.036 --> 48:32.344
The most memorable women
of the season dish dirt

48:32.387 --> 48:35.477
and tell stories
that we want to hear.

48:36.696 --> 48:39.003
Sam, you look thin.
Not again.

48:39.046 --> 48:41.396
You've lost weight.
Yeah? You've gained weight.

48:41.440 --> 48:42.963
Samantha Dale Horton.

48:43.007 --> 48:45.444
You can comment on my weight,
but I can't comment on yours?

48:45.487 --> 48:47.576
Because it's rude.
Yup, it is.

48:47.620 --> 48:50.144
Wait a minute,
he's about to
give her the flower.

48:50.188 --> 48:52.320
I say he picks the one
with the bigger chest.

48:52.364 --> 48:53.713
You say that every year.

48:53.756 --> 48:57.108
And I'm gonna keep saying it
until I'm wrong.

48:57.151 --> 49:01.242
Mama, are you gonna get
more Coke?

49:01.286 --> 49:03.984
What did you just say?
I want one too.

49:04.028 --> 49:06.944
I'll take a beer.
Can I please just
go to the bathroom?

49:14.038 --> 49:15.691
She okay, you think?

49:15.735 --> 49:17.998
She gets that
from my people.

49:18.042 --> 49:21.219
The women got bladders
the size of peas.

49:30.228 --> 49:31.316
Hey, Brandy.

49:31.359 --> 49:32.708
Hey, you gotta help me.

49:32.752 --> 49:34.710
I'm out, and I'm desperate.

49:34.754 --> 49:36.408
It's gonna take me a few days.

49:36.451 --> 49:38.018
My guy's out of town.

49:38.062 --> 49:42.196
Okay, well,
can't you just call him?
Or someone else, please?

49:42.240 --> 49:44.720
I'll make it worth your while.

49:44.764 --> 49:47.549
Well,
darling, now we're talking.

49:49.725 --> 49:52.293
[ALARM BUZZING]

50:15.403 --> 50:17.536
[SHOWER RUNNING]

50:20.278 --> 50:22.758
♪♪

50:35.119 --> 50:36.207
Yeah, I got it.

50:36.250 --> 50:39.645
Sample,
Waiting Room 1, got it.

50:39.688 --> 50:41.516
But, Mama, I don't want to.

50:41.560 --> 50:44.432
Well, you're gonna have to.
That's how
doctors look for stuff.

50:44.476 --> 50:45.955
Like what?

50:45.999 --> 50:48.393
I don't know,
the kind of stuff
they find in your pee.

50:48.436 --> 50:50.699
But I don't have to go.
You're gonna have to try.

50:50.743 --> 50:52.658
I can't.
Yes, you can.

50:52.701 --> 50:54.703
I can't.
I'll turn on the water.

50:54.747 --> 50:56.531
That doesn't help. I can't.
Try.

50:56.575 --> 50:58.707
Stop saying it!
Do you hear me?
Stop it.

50:58.751 --> 51:01.101
Stop saying it!
Stop saying it!
Stop saying it!

51:01.145 --> 51:04.235
Okay, Mama, I'll do it.
I'll try.

51:09.501 --> 51:11.851
Oh, my God, I'm sorry.

51:13.592 --> 51:15.724
I'm so sorry.

51:18.249 --> 51:20.425
Mama's just having
a bad day, okay?

51:20.468 --> 51:23.210
Go on out to the waiting room.
I'm gonna be right there.

51:23.254 --> 51:24.777
I'm sorry.

51:25.517 --> 51:27.432
I'm sorry.

51:31.610 --> 51:33.612
[SOBBING]

51:38.660 --> 51:41.359
♪♪

51:51.195 --> 51:53.371
Not tonight.

51:53.414 --> 51:55.286
I just can't.

52:19.962 --> 52:21.660
[HANDCUFFS CLICKING]

52:24.967 --> 52:26.665
You okay, Brandy?

52:26.708 --> 52:29.624
The last few weeks,
you seem kind of different.

52:29.668 --> 52:31.278
Yeah, sure, baby, I'm fine.

52:31.322 --> 52:33.933
You want
anything special today
or just the usual?

52:33.976 --> 52:37.545
No, the usual's
just fine, Brandy.

52:37.589 --> 52:41.810
Hey,
remember I was telling you
that my in-laws are in town?

52:41.854 --> 52:44.813
Yeah, Aline and Tim
from Chattanooga.

52:44.857 --> 52:46.511
Yeah.

52:46.554 --> 52:48.991
Well,
anyway, they get here and...

52:49.035 --> 52:51.820
You mind if we just
get this going?

52:51.864 --> 52:55.302
A little less talking?
I guess so.

52:55.346 --> 52:56.477
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

52:56.521 --> 52:57.826
I got a session in here.

52:57.870 --> 53:00.394
Session's over, ma'am.
Cuff them.

53:00.438 --> 53:01.526
[POLICEMEN SHOUTING
INDISTINCTLY]

53:01.569 --> 53:03.615
Well, her, anyway.

53:03.658 --> 53:06.531
You have the right
to remain silent.

53:06.574 --> 53:08.620
Anything you say
can and will be

53:08.663 --> 53:10.665
used against you
in a court of law.

53:10.709 --> 53:12.711
COP 3: Get down! COP 2: Police!

53:20.849 --> 53:22.547
What the heck
is going on here?

53:22.590 --> 53:24.331
Y'all have been
fine with us for years.

53:24.375 --> 53:26.551
Yeah, one of you's been
real fine with us.

53:26.594 --> 53:29.510
Listen,
Jacie, we don't like this
any better than you do.

53:29.554 --> 53:30.772
Oh, is that right?

53:30.816 --> 53:33.253
We got meth labs popping up
all over town.

53:33.297 --> 53:36.865
We wanna occupy ourselves
with a couple of old boys
getting happy endings?

53:36.909 --> 53:38.432
It's hilarious, isn't it?

53:38.476 --> 53:40.434
You call your
sergeant right now,

53:40.478 --> 53:42.480
and you tell him to
put a stop to this.

53:42.523 --> 53:45.700
Yeah,
and tell him Doreen says hi.

53:45.744 --> 53:48.442
This is coming
from way above him.

53:48.486 --> 53:50.705
The media got
here before we did.

53:50.749 --> 53:52.620
We have orders to search
the premises.

53:52.664 --> 53:54.883
Search away,
ain't gonna find nothing.

53:54.927 --> 53:56.537
We got this.

53:59.714 --> 54:01.760
♪♪

54:03.762 --> 54:05.503
MAN: Come on. REX: Come on, now.

54:05.546 --> 54:06.895
Carry that thing, son.

54:06.939 --> 54:09.463
Don't go out of bounds,
cut upfield.

54:09.507 --> 54:10.725
[MEN CHEERING & GRUNTING]

54:10.769 --> 54:12.466
You played with him
at UT, right?

54:12.510 --> 54:14.729
Yeah. He didn't used to be
contact-shy.

54:14.773 --> 54:17.558
We interrupt this program
to bring you breaking news

54:17.602 --> 54:19.908
of a police raid
currently in progress
in Lareena.

54:19.952 --> 54:22.433
They better have just got
Saddam Hussein.

54:22.476 --> 54:25.914
They already got him, idiot.
Well,
then the other one, then.

54:25.958 --> 54:28.743
As you can see,
going on behind me right now

54:28.787 --> 54:31.703
is a major bust of an alleged
prostitution and drug ring.

54:31.746 --> 54:34.793
Apparently, there has been
a months-long
surveillance probe

54:34.836 --> 54:36.664
conducted by Mayor Summerlin.

54:36.708 --> 54:38.536
All part of her
campaign promise

54:38.579 --> 54:40.451
to bring law and
order to Lareena.

54:40.494 --> 54:42.757
Summerlin is in
a very tight re-election race

54:42.801 --> 54:45.325
and no doubt
she hopes an event like this

54:45.369 --> 54:47.762
will help to put
her over the edge.

54:47.806 --> 54:51.897
Now we can see the police
are starting to bring out
some of the alleged johns.

54:51.940 --> 54:54.334
The poor bastards.

54:54.378 --> 54:57.032
Ho-ho-ho.
What, do they charge
by the pound?

54:57.076 --> 54:59.818
You don't have to
shake the sheets
to find her.

54:59.861 --> 55:03.430
The name of the establishment
is the Kind Touch Health Spa,

55:03.474 --> 55:06.085
but locals here say
they've long known that...

55:06.128 --> 55:08.522
Oh, my gosh.

55:08.566 --> 55:09.915
Phil, turn that off now.

55:09.958 --> 55:12.439
...becoming quite a show
for the whole neighborhood.

55:12.483 --> 55:13.919
We'll keep you updated.

55:13.962 --> 55:17.096
Okay, now we're talking.

55:17.139 --> 55:18.663
Shut up.

55:18.706 --> 55:20.578
...along with
the alleged prostitutes.

55:20.621 --> 55:22.667
Of course,
they will be held separately.

55:22.710 --> 55:24.146
The big question tonight is...

55:24.190 --> 55:27.585
Hey, Rex, she looks kind of
like your wife, doesn't she?

55:28.542 --> 55:29.935
I said, shut up.

55:29.978 --> 55:31.763
We do hope to
hear from the mayor

55:31.806 --> 55:33.634
and the police
chief for more details.

55:33.678 --> 55:35.897
They'll be holding
a press conference

55:35.941 --> 55:38.987
and of course
we'll bring that to you
as soon as it happens.

55:39.858 --> 55:41.555
♪♪

55:44.863 --> 55:47.561
I knew it would end like this.
Dee, please.

55:47.605 --> 55:49.868
No,
you bail someone out of jail,
you get to talk.

55:52.044 --> 55:54.829
At first, you did it
to save your family,

55:54.873 --> 55:57.571
I get that,
but then it was for you.

55:59.051 --> 56:00.705
You threw your whole life away

56:00.748 --> 56:03.621
for what's on your ears
and around your neck.

56:11.106 --> 56:13.413
You're home.

56:13.457 --> 56:15.807
Oh, what did I do?

56:17.112 --> 56:20.028
What am I
supposed to say to him?

56:20.072 --> 56:22.509
How am I gonna fix this?

56:24.076 --> 56:25.817
I don't know.

56:26.905 --> 56:29.386
Maybe some
things can't be fixed.

57:15.562 --> 57:17.521
Rex, I'm so sorry.

57:20.567 --> 57:23.527
I know that I've really
messed things up,

57:23.570 --> 57:25.964
and I'll do
just about anything
to make it right.

57:26.007 --> 57:27.226
So just look at me.

57:28.532 --> 57:30.185
Talk to me.

57:30.229 --> 57:34.146
Yell at me,
swear at me, hit me,
I don't care.

57:42.154 --> 57:43.982
[SNIFFLES]

57:51.293 --> 57:53.992
All night,
I've been
thinking about something.

57:55.341 --> 57:57.952
That summer after graduation?

57:57.996 --> 58:00.999
You and me going...

58:01.042 --> 58:04.176
Going to the vet
to put Barney down.

58:05.830 --> 58:08.136
I loved that dog too.

58:09.137 --> 58:11.183
And we get there,

58:11.226 --> 58:14.099
and we're sitting
in the parking lot

58:14.142 --> 58:17.798
holding that old
dog between us,

58:17.842 --> 58:22.542
petting him,
him loving the attention...

58:24.196 --> 58:27.634
and both of us knowing
it's his last day of life.

58:30.594 --> 58:32.726
And then you sang to him.

58:32.770 --> 58:34.728
That Beatles song.

58:36.338 --> 58:38.210
"In My Life."

58:39.646 --> 58:41.169
And then I...

58:41.213 --> 58:43.041
I couldn't do it.

58:43.084 --> 58:45.086
I couldn't go in.

58:46.697 --> 58:48.655
And you took him,

58:48.699 --> 58:50.701
and you carried him in...

58:52.616 --> 58:54.705
and you held him...

58:56.184 --> 58:58.056
till he died.

59:01.929 --> 59:04.018
You did that for me.

59:08.109 --> 59:12.592
And any time things got tough
with us,
I'd think of that day,

59:12.636 --> 59:15.987
and I'd think of that girl.

59:20.905 --> 59:23.864
And now when I think of you,
it's gonna be this.

59:30.131 --> 59:32.046
[SOBBING]

59:33.657 --> 59:35.267
[SOBBING]

59:44.363 --> 59:49.281
Winner of the 1999
Miss Bixby Beauty Pageant

59:49.324 --> 59:53.764
is Samantha Dale.

59:53.807 --> 59:57.245
[APPLAUSE ON TV]

01:00:02.860 --> 01:00:04.601
Mama?

01:00:05.123 --> 01:00:06.907
Thank you, Eric.

01:00:06.951 --> 01:00:08.779
Hey, what are you doing up?

01:00:08.822 --> 01:00:11.651
I heard the TV.

01:00:11.695 --> 01:00:14.698
Well, I'm sorry I woke you.
Come here.

01:00:14.741 --> 01:00:16.961
You're watching
your pageant video.

01:00:17.004 --> 01:00:18.745
Yeah.

01:00:22.009 --> 01:00:25.970
I like the part where you say
what you'd tell
the president to do

01:00:26.013 --> 01:00:28.015
to fix the Middle East.

01:00:28.059 --> 01:00:30.278
Did you ever
tell the president?

01:00:30.322 --> 01:00:31.932
No.

01:00:31.976 --> 01:00:34.935
Oddly enough, he decided
not to consult
Miss Bixby Hills

01:00:34.979 --> 01:00:37.285
about international relations.

01:00:38.417 --> 01:00:41.986
Why are you
watching this?

01:00:42.029 --> 01:00:43.857
Just revisiting
a time in my life

01:00:43.901 --> 01:00:46.338
when I felt like
I was doing everything right.

01:00:51.212 --> 01:00:52.997
You look sad.

01:00:53.040 --> 01:00:56.740
Do you want me to sing to you,
like you do when I'm sad?

01:00:56.783 --> 01:00:59.873
I think if you did that,
I just might fall apart.

01:00:59.917 --> 01:01:02.354
You're sweet, though.

01:01:02.397 --> 01:01:04.922
Then should I go back to bed?

01:01:06.140 --> 01:01:07.968
In a minute.

01:01:14.018 --> 01:01:16.803
[SOBBING QUIETLY]

01:01:30.512 --> 01:01:33.820
Do you think they're gonna
let me wear makeup in jail?

01:01:33.864 --> 01:01:36.344
I'll try to smuggle you some.

01:01:36.388 --> 01:01:38.738
Thank you for helping me.

01:01:38.782 --> 01:01:40.914
I'm your friend.

01:01:40.958 --> 01:01:43.482
I haven't been
a very good friend lately.

01:01:43.525 --> 01:01:45.789
Well, friendship
isn't quid pro quo.

01:01:46.485 --> 01:01:49.314
Wow, you are a lawyer.

01:01:49.357 --> 01:01:52.186
What's your mom
say about all this?

01:01:52.230 --> 01:01:55.929
"It's the reason you have more
than one kid. So you can
ditch the screw-ups."

01:01:55.973 --> 01:01:58.018
That sounds like your mom.

01:01:58.062 --> 01:02:01.805
All right, let's get down
to business.

01:02:01.848 --> 01:02:05.069
It seems this whole thing was
orchestrated by the mayor's
re-election team.

01:02:05.112 --> 01:02:08.159
They're trying to position her
as the champion of
traditional values.

01:02:08.202 --> 01:02:09.856
How did she even find out
about us?

01:02:09.900 --> 01:02:12.859
Know someone by the name
of Emma Hollings?

01:02:12.903 --> 01:02:14.208
Oh, my God.

01:02:14.252 --> 01:02:16.515
She went
to some religious group.

01:02:16.558 --> 01:02:19.213
Christian Fellowship Lodge.
That's it.

01:02:19.257 --> 01:02:21.389
She found a lot
of old people with

01:02:21.433 --> 01:02:23.522
time on their
hands and cell phones.

01:02:23.565 --> 01:02:26.264
They bombarded
the police with calls,
they got nowhere.

01:02:26.307 --> 01:02:28.353
Took it to city hall,
where the mayor

01:02:28.396 --> 01:02:30.311
decided it was
divine intervention.

01:02:31.835 --> 01:02:33.837
I sent her there.
This is all my fault.

01:02:33.880 --> 01:02:37.144
They're looking to charge you
with felony
promotion of prostitution

01:02:37.188 --> 01:02:39.190
and possession of cocaine.

01:02:39.233 --> 01:02:40.495
You're looking at two years.

01:02:41.453 --> 01:02:43.281
Oh, my God.

01:02:45.457 --> 01:02:46.850
Are you still using?

01:02:46.893 --> 01:02:49.417
No. Never again.

01:02:49.461 --> 01:02:51.028
I feel like dog crap.

01:02:51.071 --> 01:02:54.074
Well,
you're gonna feel agitated,
depressed.

01:02:54.118 --> 01:02:55.989
I mean,
the works for a few months,

01:02:56.033 --> 01:03:01.386
and then, honestly, periodic
cravings for
the 10 next years.

01:03:01.429 --> 01:03:05.129
Guess the first two years
will be while I'm in jail.

01:03:05.172 --> 01:03:07.000
Well, maybe not.

01:03:07.044 --> 01:03:09.437
I think we can
use this election
to our advantage.

01:03:09.481 --> 01:03:11.309
Don't they wanna look tough
on crime?

01:03:11.352 --> 01:03:13.441
But what they want more
is publicity.

01:03:13.485 --> 01:03:15.443
The more
attention that Summerlin

01:03:15.487 --> 01:03:17.489
can get from this,
the better for her.

01:03:17.532 --> 01:03:20.971
The more we help her,
the more likely
she is to help us.

01:03:21.014 --> 01:03:24.104
And the best way
to get attention is
if we have good names to give.

01:03:24.148 --> 01:03:25.453
Did you have any clients

01:03:25.497 --> 01:03:29.153
that were prominent members
of the community?

01:03:29.196 --> 01:03:33.244
Well,
yeah, but I don't wanna hurt
any of those guys.

01:03:33.287 --> 01:03:36.290
Well,
I can't worry about them,
I'm representing you.

01:03:36.334 --> 01:03:39.032
Besides,
all the johns ever get
is a slap on the wrist.

01:03:39.076 --> 01:03:41.426
There's personal
and
professional embarrassment,

01:03:41.469 --> 01:03:44.298
but they do more sleeping
on the couch than jail time.

01:03:45.952 --> 01:03:47.301
I just don't know.

01:03:47.345 --> 01:03:49.042
Well, fine.

01:03:49.086 --> 01:03:51.915
Go to jail.
Don't see your
kids for two years.

01:03:55.135 --> 01:03:59.313
Okay, tell me what you need.
That's better.

01:03:59.357 --> 01:04:01.141
And what about the girls?

01:04:01.185 --> 01:04:04.144
Is this gonna
reduce their jail time?
It might.

01:04:04.188 --> 01:04:05.972
I know it's a cash
business and your

01:04:06.016 --> 01:04:07.887
clients used a lot
of fake names, but...

01:04:07.931 --> 01:04:09.193
Not with me, they didn't.

01:04:10.716 --> 01:04:12.936
I need some good names, Sam.

01:04:12.979 --> 01:04:15.547
Truckers and frat boys
ain't gonna do a thing for us.

01:04:15.590 --> 01:04:18.985
We need our Eliot Spitzers
and Tiger Woods.

01:04:23.990 --> 01:04:25.122
[SIGHS]

01:04:25.165 --> 01:04:27.037
What about
a circuit court judge?

01:04:28.038 --> 01:04:31.345
You're kidding me. Who?

01:04:31.389 --> 01:04:33.260
Charlie Ocko.

01:04:33.304 --> 01:04:35.610
Dark hair, 6'4",
graduated cum laude from...

01:04:35.654 --> 01:04:37.917
I know who he is.

01:04:37.961 --> 01:04:39.484
I had a crush
on him for years.

01:04:42.704 --> 01:04:44.576
Well?

01:04:44.619 --> 01:04:48.928
Let's just say
sometimes small things
come in big packages.

01:04:50.016 --> 01:04:51.539
[CHUCKLES]

01:04:51.583 --> 01:04:54.238
Let's just stick
to what we can use
in court, shall we?

01:04:54.281 --> 01:04:56.109
This is great.

01:04:56.153 --> 01:04:59.417
I need you to
write down anyone else
you can think of.

01:05:03.116 --> 01:05:05.597
I'm gonna need
a lot more paper.

01:05:07.991 --> 01:05:09.253
TANYA:
What about the cuddle guy?

01:05:09.296 --> 01:05:10.558
SAM: Cuddle guy?

01:05:10.602 --> 01:05:12.169
Davis P. Lowell.

01:05:12.212 --> 01:05:15.520
Hedge fund manager, 44.
Three kids,
Karen, Kathy and Keily.

01:05:15.563 --> 01:05:19.306
Lives right here in Lareena
and likes to be
held for hours.

01:05:19.350 --> 01:05:21.700
Oh, that's kind of sweet.
Wearing only a diaper?

01:05:22.440 --> 01:05:25.530
Okay, that's less sweet.

01:05:25.573 --> 01:05:28.228
I don't know how it is
you do what you do.

01:05:28.272 --> 01:05:29.751
Well...

01:05:29.795 --> 01:05:33.016
Beats the hell
out of waitressing.

01:05:33.059 --> 01:05:35.583
Klaus Kransing, 52,
oil company lobbyist.

01:05:35.627 --> 01:05:38.369
He'd fly up every Thursday
during his wife's book club.

01:05:38.412 --> 01:05:41.198
When he'd get all
hot and bothered,
he'd speak to me in German.

01:05:41.241 --> 01:05:42.721
Nothing sounds sexy
in German.

01:05:42.764 --> 01:05:45.724
He gave her a diamond watch.
DOREEN: She earned it.

01:05:45.767 --> 01:05:48.161
I pawned it for a down payment
on Rex's Harley.

01:05:48.205 --> 01:05:51.643
Things any better
at home, darling?
Still sleeping on the couch.

01:05:51.686 --> 01:05:54.037
We're doing our best
to hide it from the kids.

01:05:54.080 --> 01:05:55.995
That's about to get
a whole lot harder.

01:05:56.039 --> 01:05:57.518
Arnie Vanderbaush, 46.

01:05:57.562 --> 01:05:59.607
He's a defense contractor
from El Paso.

01:05:59.651 --> 01:06:01.479
And I think that's it.

01:06:02.349 --> 01:06:05.048
What about Jim Reed?

01:06:05.091 --> 01:06:08.399
What, Carol "the
bitch of Bixby Hills'"
husband, Jim Reed?

01:06:08.442 --> 01:06:12.055
He came in,
but I sent him home.
He's been a regular for years.

01:06:12.098 --> 01:06:16.320
As much as I'd like
to stick it to Carol, please
don't put him on the list.

01:06:16.363 --> 01:06:17.625
Okay.

01:06:17.669 --> 01:06:20.193
Okay.

01:06:20.237 --> 01:06:22.282
I mean, this is incredible.

01:06:22.326 --> 01:06:24.023
If we play this right,
we're looking

01:06:24.067 --> 01:06:25.546
at minimal time
for all of you.

01:06:25.590 --> 01:06:27.984
How many names we got?

01:06:28.549 --> 01:06:31.161
Sixty-nine.

01:06:31.204 --> 01:06:33.163
That's, uh...
Appropriate?

01:06:33.206 --> 01:06:36.818
That's the word.
Look,
I'm gonna get this formatted.

01:06:36.862 --> 01:06:39.778
We are gonna walk it over
to the mayor's
office personally.

01:06:39.821 --> 01:06:41.649
And her team
has already tipped

01:06:41.693 --> 01:06:43.477
the press off.
They know it's coming.

01:06:48.352 --> 01:06:50.745
[ORGAN PLAYING]

01:06:52.530 --> 01:06:57.404
I always knew that Sam Horton
was nothing but trash.

01:07:01.626 --> 01:07:04.368
You know, I got
a real common name, honey.

01:07:04.411 --> 01:07:07.110
A lot of guys around here
got my name.

01:07:09.286 --> 01:07:12.332
Better hope none of them
are on the list.

01:07:15.509 --> 01:07:17.511
Good morning.

01:07:17.555 --> 01:07:19.687
I heard my gynecologist
was on the list.

01:07:19.731 --> 01:07:22.386
I don't even know
what to make of that.

01:07:22.429 --> 01:07:25.563
Well,
if my husband's on that list,
I'm gonna take all his stuff,

01:07:25.606 --> 01:07:28.392
put it on his bass boat
and set it on fire.

01:07:28.435 --> 01:07:30.133
Screw that.

01:07:30.176 --> 01:07:34.267
Set his stuff on fire, sure,
but sell the bass boat, girl.

01:07:34.311 --> 01:07:36.617
You can get good money
for that thing.

01:07:36.661 --> 01:07:38.706
Ooh-whee, you're right
about that. Heh.

01:07:38.750 --> 01:07:40.404
Don't this
remind you about what

01:07:40.447 --> 01:07:42.058
happened in
Odessa a few years ago?

01:07:42.884 --> 01:07:45.278
Yeah.
Heads up.

01:07:48.760 --> 01:07:49.848
Poor thing.

01:07:49.891 --> 01:07:51.371
Can you imagine?

01:07:51.415 --> 01:07:54.418
Still showing up for work,
bless her heart.

01:07:54.461 --> 01:07:57.551
I heard there's
a lot of big shots
on that list.

01:07:57.595 --> 01:08:00.728
Businessmen, doctors, lawyers.

01:08:00.772 --> 01:08:04.732
Lawyers?
Those gals must have been
really hard up for cash.

01:08:04.776 --> 01:08:07.126
Some things even a hooker
shouldn't have to do.

01:08:07.170 --> 01:08:09.128
[BOTH LAUGHING]

01:08:09.172 --> 01:08:12.131
But we don't wanna stay
at Grandma Sarah's house.

01:08:12.175 --> 01:08:14.655
She thinks apples
are for dessert.

01:08:14.699 --> 01:08:16.743
She makes us
go outside and play.

01:08:16.787 --> 01:08:18.746
Okay, kids, that's enough.

01:08:18.790 --> 01:08:22.140
You say your goodbyes
to your mama. We got
a long ride ahead of us.

01:08:22.185 --> 01:08:23.969
Why can't she come with us?

01:08:24.011 --> 01:08:28.191
Your mama can't
leave town right now.
We've been all over this, son.

01:08:28.234 --> 01:08:30.323
That's right.
Listen to your daddy.
Come here.

01:08:30.367 --> 01:08:31.759
Come here. Ooh.

